The National Directorate of Employment on Friday trained and empowered 1850 people on sustainable agricultural development.  The Director General of the National Directorate of Employment (NDE), Nasiru Argungu, who spoke at the event said that the federal government is committed to diversifying the country’s economy through articulate framework in agriculture.  Argungu, said that the program, Sustainable Agricultural Development Training Scheme, was aimed at training and empowering Nigerians who have deep commitment in agricultural program.  Represented by the Imo state Coordinator of NDE, Ngozi Ihenacho, the Director General said that 50 people from state plus the Federal Capital Territory were empowered under the scheme.  The DG said that President Muhammadu Buhari was committed to improving the country’s economy beyond reliance on oil.